The paper discusses the creation of new indices to measure the quality of scientific research, with a focus on collaboration and dissemination of knowledge. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), computational biology (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computer engineering (cs.CE). However, given the emphasis on collaboration and dissemination, cs.DL and cs.CY are the most likely sub-categories.
